# Security Baseline — {Agent Name}

## Identity & access

- Authentication mechanism for the platform (e.g., Azure AD, Entra ID)
- Service principal / managed identity conventions
- Secret storage (Key Vault, environment variables, etc.)

## Authorisation

- Platform-specific security model (e.g., CE security roles + privilege matrix, F&O duties + privileges, Power BI RLS + OLS)
- Principle of least privilege
- Role assignment conventions

## Data protection

- Data at rest (encryption, sensitivity labels)
- Data in transit (TLS minimum, certificate management)
- PII / sensitive data handling

## Audit

- Audit configuration per platform
- Log retention policy
- Access review cadence

## Per-feature security review

Every feature's spec includes §6 Security with:
- Privilege matrix per role / entity / capability
- Audit configuration changes
- Sensitive data fields
- Authentication / authorisation deltas vs the baseline above

`doc_lint` rules enforce presence of §6 Security in every spec.

## Multilingual & accessibility

- Language code conventions per `project.config.yaml multilingual`
- Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA minimum for UI artefacts)
